subjectkey: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
src_subject_id: Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
interview_date: Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
interview_age: Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
phase_ct: Current Phase. Phase patient was in at the time of the assessment Phase 4 refers to the follow-up phase.
visday: Number of days from study baseline to date of visit
bat11: Computerized Test of Visuospatial Working Memory
neur1: Is English the patient's first language?
neur2a: WRAT-3 not done at this visit
neur3a: Controlled Oral Word Association Test (COWAT) Number of correct words generated in category F
neur3b: Controlled Oral Word Association Test (COWAT) Number of correct words generated in category A
neur3c: Controlled Oral Word Association Test (COWAT) Number of correct words generated in category S
neur4a: Category Instances: Number of correct words generated in category Animals
neur4b: Category Instances: Number of correct words generated in category Fruits
neur4c: Category Instances: Number of correct words generated in category Vegetables
neur7a: Hopkins Verbal Learning Test: Number of items recalled on trial 1
neur7b: Hopkins Verbal Learning Test: Number of items recalled on trial 2
neur7c: Hopkins Verbal Learning Test: Number of items recalled on trial 3
neur8: Facial Emotion Discrimination Task: Number of faces correctly discriminated
neur9: WAIS-R Digit Symbol Test raw score
neur6: Letter-number Sequencing: Number of correct sequences
neur10a: Grooved Pegboard: Number of pegs successfully inserted on  trial 1
neur10b: Grooved Pegboard: Number of pegs successfully inserted on  trial 2
neur11a: Continuous Performance Test (CPT) d-prime score: two digit
neur11b: Continuous Performance Test (CPT) d-prime score: three digit
neur11c: Continuous Performance Test (CPT) d-prime score: four digit
neur11d: Continuous Performance Test (CPT) Reaction time score ms: two digit
neur11e: Continuous Performance Test (CPT) Reaction time score ms: three digit
neur11f: Continuous Performance Test (CPT) Reaction time score ms: four digit
neur12a: Computerized Test of Visuospatial Working Memory: Mean error for each trial mm: no delay
neur12b: Computerized Test of Visuospatial Working Memory: Mean error for each trial mm: 5 second delay
neur12c: Computerized Test of Visuospatial Working Memory: Mean error for each trial mm: 15 second delay
neur13a: Wisconsin Card Sorting Test (64-P): Number of perseverative errors
neur13b: Wisconsin Card Sorting Test (64-P): Number of completed categories
neur13c: Wisconsin Card Sorting Test (64-P): Additional consecutive cards in the final category
neur8_c: NEUR8 in Category by grouping score 15
p_flag: Flag for Patients With Enough Data
neur5_s: WISCR Mazes Standardized response for NEUR5
neu12_sr: "Reversed sign of NEUR12_S, the standardized response for the following calculation: (average of 5 second delay and 15 second delay) (no delay), with invalid data set to missing"
mneur34: "Mean of the standardized to baseline responses to NEUR3A, NEUR3B,NEUR3C and NEUR4A, NEUR4B,NEUR4C"
mneur10: Mean of the standardized to baseline responses to NEUR10A and NEUR10B
mneur13: "Mean of the reversed standardized to baseline response to NEUR13A, and the standardized to baseline response to (NEUR13B + NEUR13C/10)"
n_flag: Neuro Comp Score: Complete Data at Test Level
verbal_s: "Verbal Domain Score Standardized to baseline Mean of (NEUR7A_S, NEUR7B_S, NEUR7C_S)"
vigil_s: "Vigilance Domain Score Standardized to baseline Mean of (NEUR11A_S, NEUR11B_S, NEUR11C_S)"
speed_s: "Processing Speed Domain Score Standardized to baseline mean of (MNEUR34, MNEUR10, NEUR9_S)"
reason_s: Reasoning Domain Score Standardized to Baseline Mean of (MNEUR13 and NEUR5_S)
memory_s: "Working Memory Domain Score Standardized to baseline Mean of (NEU12_SR,NEUR6_S)"
neuro_ss: "Neurocognitive Composite Score Created variable: Standardized to baseline Mean of (VERBAL_S, VIGIL_S, SPEED_S, REASON_S, MEMORY_S)"
collection_title: collection_title
